To the person who still has a problem with WanDB 403 permission denied issue.  The problem may come from having multiple WanDB accounts and switching the account.  I use the below method to check my API key and resolve the permission denied issue.
1. Check if you have multiple login WanDB accounts on WanDB.
2. Login to WanDB on the http://https://wandb.ai/
3. Check your API key on the user setting section when you to the website
4. Check your API key store in the .env on the "compute-subnet" folder.
5. Check your API key store in the "home/account/.netrc"
6. All the above API keys must be the same.  Otherwise, you may encounter a permission error when you switch between multiple WanDB accounts.
7. You can check the https://wandb.ai/your_account_name to see which miner/validator_hotkey project you created on WanDB to see if they are matched with your configured API key.
